articles.author: Stella Qiu
articles.description: Asian shares tracked Wall Street futures higher on Friday as Amazon provided some welcome earnings relief, while bonds were able to sustain a rally amid signs U.S. inflation was easing.
articles.title: Asian shares track US futures higher, bonds hold gains

articles.author: Luc Cohen, Jody Godoy
articles.description: FTX founder Sam Bankman-Fried testified on Thursday at his fraud trial outside the jury's presence that lawyers at his now-bankrupt cryptocurrency exchange were involved in key decisions at the heart of the case, as he sought to distance himself from responsibility for any wrongdoing.
articles.title: Sam Bankman-Fried testifies lawyers were involved in key FTX decisions

articles.author: David Shepardson
articles.description: General Motors' (GM.N) driverless car unit Cruise said late Thursday it will suspend all operations nationwide after California regulators this week ordered the robotaxi operator to remove its driverless cars from state roads.
articles.title: GM Cruise unit suspends all driverless operations after California ban

articles.author: Leika Kihara, Takahiko Wada
articles.description: Core consumer inflation in Japan's capital Tokyo, considered a leading indicator of nationwide trends, unexpectedly accelerated in October, a sign of broadening price pressures that may keep alive expectations of near-term end to ultra-low interest rates.
articles.title: Core inflation in Japan's capital unexpectedly accelerates, BOJ in spotlight

articles.author: Deborah Sophia
articles.description: Investors will look for signs that U.S. fast-food chains, already contending with inflation-stung consumers preferring to dine at home, will also have to grapple with the explosive popularity of weight-loss drugs.
articles.title: Weight-loss drug worries add to US restaurants' weak traffic woes

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Sundar Pichai, chief executive of Alphabet (GOOGL.O) and its subsidiary Google, will testify on Monday in the once-in-a generation antitrust fight over Google's dominance of search and some parts of search advertising.
articles.title: Google CEO Sundar Pichai to testify Monday in US Google antitrust trial

articles.author: Abigail Summerville
articles.description: GOJO Industries, the maker of Purell hand sanitizer, said on Thursday it would refinance its debt after sources told Reuters that negotiations about the sale of the company to paper and building products manufacturer Georgia-Pacific fell through.
articles.title: Purell maker to refinance debt after failed Georgia-Pacific deal talks

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israel said on Friday military raids into Gaza were preparing "the next stage of the operation", amid fears that a ground invasion of the Palestinian enclave could spark a wider conflict and a media report of a missile hitting an Egyptian border town.
articles.title: Israeli military raid Gaza to prepare 'next stage'; report missile hit Egyptian town

articles.author: Gabriella Borter, Brad Brooks
articles.description: Dr. Richard King was driving home from the Central Maine Medical Center on Wednesday night when he received an urgent call from a fellow trauma surgeon alerting him that victims of a mass casualty event were flooding the hospital.
articles.title: Inside the Maine hospital that treated shooting victims

articles.author: Joseph Ax
articles.description: A federal judge on Thursday ordered Georgia lawmakers to draw a new congressional map for the 2024 election, ruling that the current Republican-backed plan illegally diluted Black votes in violation of the Voting Rights Act.
articles.title: US judge orders new congressional map in Georgia, citing harm to Black voters
